body:
New Post: The Marvel Avengers Book Tag

Seeing as the glory that Endgame has been released, I thought why not have a go at the Marvel Book Tag? I found this over on RiverMoose-Reads and, well, it seemed fitting. FYI I loved Endgame, it’s currently my favourite film of the year and it deserves ALL of the awards.

So, let’s go.

Iron Man – a book that made you laugh out loud:


A Girl Called Shameless

I laughed so much and so hard…

summary: Friendly reminder that it was Peter Quill's first time visiting Earth in 31 years since his mother died and the Russos didn't...
body: Friendly reminder that it was Peter Quill’s first time visiting Earth in 31 years since his mother died and the Russos didn’t give us a scene where he went to Missouri to visit his mom’s grave, going through the other mixtapes that his mom made and catching up with his remaining family members before leaving the planet.
